# Microsoft (Entra ID) SSO — "Login with Microsoft"
#
# MSAL_CLIENT_ID/MSAL_TENANT_ID below already match the Azure App Registration
# used by watchcase_tracker/sso.py, but the CLIENT SECRET is never checked in
# (it is a credential, not a public ID) and was missing entirely from this repo
# and from web.config — that is why "Login with Microsoft" returns
# "SSO not configured." (see watchcase_tracker/sso.py:17-19).
#
# Fill in the real value from: Azure Portal → App registrations →
# (the app with Client ID 54a2fd19-0009-4e29-9d7b-b33e9ae8fbfa) →
# Certificates & secrets → Client secrets → (create/copy the secret VALUE,
# not the Secret ID). Then restart the app/app pool for it to take effect.

# MSAL_TENANT_ID=04132f71-f746-4a5b-a30e-66ea6d16714c


MSAL_CLIENT_ID=54a2fd19-0009-4e29-9d7b-b33e9ae8fbfa
MSAL_TENANT_ID=organizations
MSAL_CLIENT_SECRET=YOUR_SECRET

# AADSTS50011 fix: the redirect URI Django builds must be registered in
